quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  29,24,"So the answer of his (Ibrahim’s) people was nothing except that they said, “Kill him or burn him.” But Allah saved him from the fire. There are certainly signs in that for a people who believe"
  29,25,"And he said, “You have taken (for worship) only idols, besides Allah. Your mutual love is in the life of this world, then on the day of resurrection some of you will reject others and some of you will curse others, and your settling place will be the fire and you will not have any helpers.”"
  29,26,"So Lut believed in him and said, “I am a migrant towards my Fosterer, He is certainly the Mighty, the Wise.”"
  29,27,"And We granted to him (i.e. Ibrahim), Ishaq and Yaqub and made the prophet hood (to remain) in his descendants and (also) the book. And We gave him his reward in the world, and in the hereafter he will certainly be among the righteous"
  29,28,"And Lut when he said to his people, “You certainly commit an indecency which no one in the worlds had committed before you"
  29,29,"What! do you come to males and cut off the way (for committing robbery) and in your assemblies you commit things not recognised (as good)?” So the answer of his people was nothing except that they said, “Bring upon us the punishment of Allah if you are of the truthful ones.”"
  29,30,"He said, “My Fosterer! help me against the corrupt people.”"